    "Goh Cheng Liang gets the bulk of his wealth from a stake in Japan's Nippon Paint Holdings, the fourth largest paint manufacturer in the world.",
    "Goh started making paints in a small factory in Singapore before he went on to partner with Japan's Nippon Paint in 1962.",
    "Goh's son, Hup Jin, was appointed chairman of Nippon Paint in March 2018 and also runs their privately held joint venture, Nipsea.",
    "In 2019, Nippon Paint acquired DuluxGroup, Australia's largest paint manufacturer, for $2.7 billion and Turkey's Betek Boya for $247 million."
